                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.809,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 140790,
                                "text": "Next Justice Kennedy has our opinion in case 08-1470, Burghuis versus Thompkins."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.809,
                        "stop": 292.963,
                        "byte_start": 140790,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15113,
                            "name": "Anthony M. Kennedy",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/anthony_m_kennedy",
                            "last_name": "Kennedy",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2757,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 572162400,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2757"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32679,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 47100,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/anthony_kennedy_1_3.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10147,
                            "identifier": "anthony_m_kennedy"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.809,
                                "stop": 15.341,
                                "byte_start": 140790,
                                "byte_stop": 166912,
                                "text": "After a jury trial in a Michigan State Court, Van Chester Tompkins was convicted of murder."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.341,
                                "stop": 24.517,
                                "byte_start": 166912,
                                "byte_stop": 203588,
                                "text": "In this habeas corpus proceeding, the Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit ruled that there had been two separate constitutional errors to this trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.517,
                                "stop": 33.923,
                                "byte_start": 203588,
                                "byte_stop": 241204,
                                "text": "First, they determined that a statement by the accused relied on at trial by the prosecution had been elicited in violation of Miranda versus Arizona."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.923,
                                "stop": 42.904,
                                "byte_start": 241204,
                                "byte_stop": 277149,
                                "text": "Second, it found that failure to ask for an instruction relating to testimony from an accomplice was ineffective assistance by defense counsel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.904,
                                "stop": 47.412,
                                "byte_start": 277149,
                                "byte_stop": 295121,
                                "text": "We conclude that the Court of Appeals erred in both of its rulings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.412,
                                "stop": 50.229,
                                "byte_start": 295121,
                                "byte_stop": 306406,
                                "text": "We begin with the Miranda issue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.229,
                                "stop": 56.748,
                                "byte_start": 306406,
                                "byte_stop": 332528,
                                "text": "After arresting Thompkins, two detectives interrogated him and one was Detective Helgert."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.748,
                                "stop": 62.384,
                                "byte_start": 332528,
                                "byte_stop": 355098,
                                "text": "Helgert presented Tompkins with a written form derived from the Miranda rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.384,
                                "stop": 73.336,
                                "byte_start": 355098,
                                "byte_stop": 398879,
                                "text": "The form was broken down into five parts at the request of Detective Helgert, Thompkins himself read one of these parts out loud the others were read aloud by Helgert."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.336,
                                "stop": 76.523,
                                "byte_start": 398879,
                                "byte_stop": 411627,
                                "text": "The officers then began the interrogation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.523,
                                "stop": 85.463,
                                "byte_start": 411627,
                                "byte_stop": 447363,
                                "text": "At no point did Thompkins say he wanted to remain silent or that he did not wanted to talk to the police or that he wanted an attorney."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.463,
                                "stop": 91.85,
                                "byte_start": 447363,
                                "byte_stop": 472963,
                                "text": "He was largely silent during the investigation and it lasted about three hours."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.85,
                                "stop": 103.405,
                                "byte_start": 472963,
                                "byte_stop": 519147,
                                "text": "About two and three quarters hours into the interrogation, two hours and 45 minutes Helgert asked Thompkins, do you pray to God to forgive you for shooting that boy down."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.405,
                                "stop": 112.363,
                                "byte_start": 519147,
                                "byte_stop": 554987,
                                "text": "Thompkins answered yes and looked away and that was the statement that was used against Thompkins at his trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.363,
                                "stop": 118.1,
                                "byte_start": 554987,
                                "byte_stop": 577975,
                                "text": "Thompkins argued that he invoked his right to remain silent by not saying anything for a sufficient period of time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.1,
                                "stop": 122.685,
                                "byte_start": 577975,
                                "byte_stop": 596261,
                                "text": "So that the interrogation should have ceased before he made his inculpatory statements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.685,
                                "stop": 125.23,
                                "byte_start": 596261,
                                "byte_stop": 606396,
                                "text": "This argument is unpersuasive."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.23,
                                "stop": 130.813,
                                "byte_start": 606396,
                                "byte_stop": 628757,
                                "text": "To invoke the Miranda right to remain silent an accused must do so unambiguously."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.813,
                                "stop": 143.467,
                                "byte_start": 628757,
                                "byte_stop": 679434,
                                "text": "A requirement of an unambiguous invocation of Miranda rights results in an objective inquiry that avoids difficulties of proof and provides guidance to officers on how to proceed in the face of ambiguity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.467,
                                "stop": 147.625,
                                "byte_start": 679434,
                                "byte_stop": 696048,
                                "text": "Thompkins did not say that he wanted to remain silent or that he did not want to talk with the police."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.625,
                                "stop": 153.589,
                                "byte_start": 696048,
                                "byte_stop": 719872,
                                "text": "Had he made either of these simple statements, he would have invoked his right to cut off questioning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.589,
                                "stop": 180.144,
                                "byte_start": 719872,
                                "byte_stop": 826138,
                                "text": "Now, even absent the accused invocation of the right to remain silent, a statement by the accused during custodial interrogation is still inadmissible at trial unless the prosecution can establish that the accused in fact knowingly and voluntarily waive Miranda rights when making the statement and Thompkins contend that he did not -- contends that he did not waive his right to remain silent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.144,
                                "stop": 194.88,
                                "byte_start": 826138,
                                "byte_stop": 885070,
                                "text": "The course of decisions since Miranda informed by the application of Miranda warnings in the whole course of law-enforcement demonstrates that waivers can be established even absent formal or express statements of waiver."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 194.88,
                                "stop": 202.207,
                                "byte_start": 885070,
                                "byte_stop": 914328,
                                "text": "The main purpose of Miranda is to ensure that the accused is advised of and understands the right to remain silent and the right to counsel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 202.207,
                                "stop": 212.951,
                                "byte_start": 914328,
                                "byte_stop": 957377,
                                "text": "Thus the Miranda rule and its requirements are met if a suspect receives adequate Miranda warnings, understands them, and has an opportunity to invoke the rights before giving any answers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.951,
                                "stop": 216.477,
                                "byte_start": 957377,
                                "byte_stop": 971483,
                                "text": "The record in this case shows that Thompkins waived his right to remain silent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 216.477,
                                "stop": 219.73,
                                "byte_start": 971483,
                                "byte_stop": 984440,
                                "text": "There is no contention that Thompkins did not understand his rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 219.73,
                                "stop": 226.721,
                                "byte_start": 984440,
                                "byte_stop": 1012443,
                                "text": "Thompkins was given a form that listed his rights and all of the rights were read aloud one by Thompkins and the others by Detective Helgert."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 226.721,
                                "stop": 236.468,
                                "byte_start": 1012443,
                                "byte_stop": 1051418,
                                "text": "Thompkins\u2019 answers to Detective Helgert\u0027s question about whether Thompkins prayed to God for forgiveness for shooting the victim is a course of conduct indicating waiver of the right to remain silent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 236.468,
                                "stop": 244.713,
                                "byte_start": 1051418,
                                "byte_stop": 1084332,
                                "text": "There is no evidence that Thompkins statement coerced, nor were the police required to obtain a waiver of Thompkins\u2019 right to remain silent before interrogating him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 244.713,
                                "stop": 252.116,
                                "byte_start": 1084332,
                                "byte_stop": 1114008,
                                "text": "In 1979, in North Carolina versus Paul Butler, this Court rejected that argument and we adhere to that decision today."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 252.116,
                                "stop": 259.359,
                                "byte_start": 1114008,
                                "byte_stop": 1142951,
                                "text": "In sum the State Court\u2019s decisions rejecting -- decision rejecting Thompkins\u0027 Miranda claim was correct."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.359,
                                "stop": 272.087,
                                "byte_start": 1142951,
                                "byte_stop": 1193838,
                                "text": "The second issue in this case is whether Thompkins counsel provided ineffective assistance by failing to request the limiting instruction regarding how the jury could consider the outcome of an accomplice\u2019s trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 272.087,
                                "stop": 280.793,
                                "byte_start": 1193838,
                                "byte_stop": 1228737,
                                "text": "For reasons given in our opinion the record establishes that it was not reasonably likely that the instruction would have made any difference in light of all the other evidence of guilt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 280.793,
                                "stop": 283.133,
                                "byte_start": 1228737,
                                "byte_stop": 1238037,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Court of Appeals is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 283.133,
                                "stop": 286.436,
                                "byte_start": 1238037,
                                "byte_stop": 1251307,
                                "text": "The case is remanded with instructions to deny the petition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 286.436,
                                "stop": 292.963,
                                "byte_start": 1251307,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Stevens, Ginsburg and Breyer have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
